# 🎵 C++ YouTube & Local Music Player

A simple, lightweight CLI music player built in C++ that supports streaming audio from YouTube and playing local files.

## 🚀 Features
- **YouTube Integration**: Download and play audio directly from YouTube links (no ads!).
- **Local File Support**: Play any `.mp3` or `.wav` file from your computer.
- **Persistent Playlist**: Your playlist is automatically saved to `playlist.txt` and reloaded on startup.
- **Volume Control**: Adjustable volume (0-100%).
- **Audio Management**: Stops previous tracks before starting new ones to prevent overlapping.

## 🛠️ Prerequisites
To compile and run this application, you need:
1. **C++ Compiler**: (e.g., MinGW/g++ for Windows).
2. **FFmpeg**: Required for audio extraction from YouTube. [Download here](https://ffmpeg.org/download.html).
3. **yt-dlp**: Required for downloading YouTube content. [Download here](https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp).

## 📁 Directory Structure
For the program to work correctly, set up your folders as follows:
```text
AudioApp/
├── main.cpp
├── miniaudio.h
├── playlist.txt (auto-generated)
├── songs/          <-- Folder for downloaded songs
│   └── .gitkeep
├── knihovny/       <-- Put external tools here
│   ├── yt-dlp.exe
│   ├── ffmpeg.exe
│   ├── ffprobe.exe
│   └── .gitkeep
└── README.md